  <summary date="2020-02-24T13:49:42Z" status="Introduced in House">Payment Choice Act of 2019 

This bill makes it unlawful for a person selling goods or services at retail to (1) refuse to accept U.S. cash for the goods or services, (2) post signs or notices stating that cash payment is unaccepted, or (3) charge a higher price to a customer who pays by cash.</summary>
